We had gotten permission from a store and the police in a small town, but our actor couldn't make the shoot so we had to reschedule in a hurry. We found a store in San Francisco, but we didn't alert the police, because we knew we'd have to pay them (since it was San Francisco), and we thought we could get in and out in a hurry. Unfortunately, some neighbors saw us and called the cops. Eight cop cars showed up and the police forced us at gunpoint to lay on the ground. Not until they had cuffed us and confiscated our plastic gun did they listen to our explanation that we were shooting a movie. We had to agree that we should have notified them, or at least blocked the door and put a sign on it so that no one could see into the store. We got the shot, though, as well as a good story and some free publicity in the paper. But the moral of the lesson is still "get a permit."

5/26/2004 4:23:15 PM uite ce fiolm am luat Renowned Spanish director Pedro Almodóvar made his big-screen debut with this zany, provocative film. Carmen Maura stars as Pepi, a crazy Madrid slacker whose friends include Luci (Eva Siva), the masochistic wife of a bullying cop, and 16-year-old Bom (Olvido Gara), the lesbian sadist rocker that Luci leaves her husband for. Lots of crazy vignettes and characters parade by in this melange of outrageousness which includes a bored bearded lady (Kiti Manver), a sex organ measurement contest (presided over by Almodóvar himself), golden showers, drag-queens, drugs, punk rock shows, and a series of commercials for some very special underwear. Working with an obviously low budget and limited means, Almodóvar still succeeds admirably in both shocking and delighting unsuspecting audiences, especially with the help of the splendidly high-spirited performances from all his actors, particularly Maura in the first of their many collaborations.

7/5/2004 3:03:45 AM ala care a intrat pe teren era suporter al barcelonei. Si astia au boala pe figo ca s-a dus la real madrid Mai ales dupa ce, în minutul 85, un suporter catalan a patruns în teren si i-a aruncat în fata un steag al Barcelonei. Gestul a fost clar. Figo era vinovat de acest esec incredibil. Apoi, fanul i-a aratat cum se înscrie. A sarit pur si simplu în plasa, înainte de a fi prins de stewarzi. „Vreau sa fiu celebru!” Cine e acest straniu personaj în blugi si cu caciula rosie care l-a înjosit pe Figo? Numele sau este Jaume Marquet Cot, un catalan suporter înrait al Barcelonei, al carui scop în viata este, asa cum singur o spune, "Sa fiu cunoscut, sa fiu celebru". Idolii sai sînt James Dean, meteoricul actor american, si inegalabilul pictor spaniol Salvador Dali. Marquet, nonconformistul fan care obisnuieste sa disturbe mari evenimente, nu doar sportive, a adunat poze cu o multime de personalit de personalitati ale Barcelonei. Printre ele, chiar Luis Figo, alaturi de sotia lui, Helene. Conversation started at 7/5/2004 7:17:07 PM

}

}
}
}
}
